title: Inhalation and ingestion of other objects causing obstruction of respiratory tract
chapter: External causes of morbidity and mortality
category: Inhalation and ingestion of other objects causing obstruction of respiratory tract
inclusion: asphyxia by any object, except food or vomitus, entering by nose or mouth
choked on any object, except food or vomitus, entering by nose or mouth
suffocation by any object, except food or vomitus, entering by nose or mouth
aspiration and inhalation of foreign body, except food or vomitus (into respiratory tract), NOS
compression of trachea by foreign body in oesophagus
interruption of respiration by foreign body in oesophagus
obstruction of respiration by foreign body in oesophagus
obstruction of pharynx by foreign body
exclusion: injury, except asphyxia or obstruction of respiratory tract, caused by foreign body
obstruction of oesophagus by foreign body without mention of asphyxia or obstruction of respiratory tract
